{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, their ability to autonomously adapt to new tasks with little fine-tuning is also clearly organismic.",
    "A mechanism's functionality is very rigid.",
    "This, then, could be the neat metaphysical explanation of why LLMs lack intentions: they are mechanistic artifacts, which means that they are on a par with watches in terms of their teleological structure and moral autonomy: They lack autonomous goal-setting.",
    "They squarely fall on the wrong side of the Kantian bifurcation between mechanisms and organisms.",
    "To the Kant of the Third Critique, it was clear that moral autonomy is available only to an organism, never to a mechanism."
  ]
}